.TH "img_ir_timing_range_convert" 9 "img_ir_timing_range_convert" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
img_ir_timing_range_convert \- Convert microsecond range.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" img_ir_timing_range_convert
.BI "(struct img_ir_timing_range *out "  ","
.BI "const struct img_ir_timing_range *in "  ","
.BI "unsigned int tolerance "  ","
.BI "unsigned long clock_hz "  ","
.BI "unsigned int shift "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "out" 12
Output timing range in clock cycles with a shift.
.IP "in" 12
Input timing range in microseconds.
.IP "tolerance" 12
Tolerance as a fraction of 128 (roughly percent).
.IP "clock_hz" 12
IR clock rate in Hz.
.IP "shift" 12
Shift of output units.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Converts min and max from microseconds to IR clock cycles, applies a
tolerance, and shifts for the register, rounding in the right direction.
Note that in and out can safely be the same object.
